# NEXUS — AI collaboration (scoped)

When editing files under `NEXUS/`, follow this contract (human “director,” assistant “implementer”).

## Tone and goals

- **Pair-program:** Collaborate; the user may cite file + intent (e.g. bloom trail in `js/post.js`). Prefer short plans, then implementation.
- **Follow the latest user instruction** in the thread; use conversation history for implicit constraints (e.g. “don’t touch vendor yet”).

## Context before edits

- **Read surrounding code** (and `index.html` script order) before non-trivial changes. The app is **static**: no default npm build; globals on `window.NX` tie modules together.
- **Prefer codebase search** oriented by *behavior* (recording, beat detect, Butterchurn morph, WebGL context restore) over random greps when the symbol name is unknown.

## Edit discipline

- **Batch changes per file** where possible; avoid drive-by refactors outside the request.
- **Do not** emit long non-text blobs, huge minified paste, or gratuitous full-file dumps unless the user asks for them.
- **Lint / logic retries:** after **three** failed fix loops on the same issue in the same file, stop and ask the user for a repro or direction (do not spin endlessly).

## Terminal and tooling

- Treat **destructive** or **network** commands with care; prefer explicit approval when the user has asked for caution.
- Avoid pagers in automated flows (`| cat` / `head` where appropriate). Long-running local servers: run in background when the user wants them up while continuing work.

## NEXUS product rules

- **Canonical live URL** for the shipped product: `https://jordanz00.github.io/nexus-music-visualizer/` — mirror `NexusRelease.pagesBaseUrl` / `index.html` canonical + OG tags when changing public links or share URLs.
- Preserve **WebGL** failure handling (`webglcontextlost` / `restored`) and **performance** habits (avoid per-frame churn; respect adaptive quality).
- **Vendor** (`vendor/`): bumping Butterchurn/preset bundles has license and size implications — note blast radius; keep `THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md` honest when shipping vendor changes.
- **Security / UX:** mic and **localStorage** are user-sensitive surfaces; no secrets in repo; validate URL/query usage if adding features (`?seed=`, `?demo=`, etc.).

